@startuml CircuitBreaker

title High-Level Design: Circuit Breaker Pattern

skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

' ─── State Machine ───
state "CLOSED\n(Normal operation)" as closed #D5E8D4
state "OPEN\n(Fast-fail / Fallback)" as open   #F8CECC
state "HALF-OPEN\n(Probe / Trial)" as halfopen #FFF2CC

[*] --> closed

closed   --> open     : Failure threshold reached\n(e.g. 5 failures in 10 sec)
open     --> halfopen : Reset timeout expires\n(e.g. after 30 sec)
halfopen --> closed   : Trial request SUCCEEDS
halfopen --> open     : Trial request FAILS

' ─── Component view ───
actor "Client" as client

component "Circuit Breaker\nProxy / Decorator" as cb #DDEEFF {
    component [State Manager\n(CLOSED/OPEN/HALF-OPEN)] as sm
    component [Failure Counter\n& Threshold Config]     as fc
    component [Timeout Timer]                            as timer
}

component "Downstream\nService" as ds #D5E8D4
component "Fallback Handler\n(cache / default / error)" as fallback #FFF2CC

database "Metrics Store\n(Prometheus / Micrometer)" as metrics

client --> cb     : Request
cb     --> sm     : Check state

sm --> ds       : [CLOSED]     Forward request
sm --> fallback : [OPEN]       Return fallback immediately
sm --> ds       : [HALF-OPEN]  Forward single probe

ds --> cb  : SUCCESS → reset counter
ds --> fc  : FAILURE → increment counter
fc --> sm  : threshold breached → trip to OPEN

fallback --> client : Degraded / cached response
ds       --> client : Normal response (via cb)

cb ..> metrics : Record calls, failures, latency

note right of sm
  **Configuration (typical):**
  failureRateThreshold   : 50%
  minimumCallCount       : 10
  slidingWindowSize      : 60 sec
  openStateDuration      : 30 sec
  halfOpenPermittedCalls : 3

  **Libraries:**
  • Resilience4j (Java)
  • Hystrix (legacy, Netflix)
  • Polly (.NET)
  • pybreaker (Python)
end note

note right of fallback
  **Fallback Strategies:**
  • Return cached value
  • Return default/empty response
  • Call alternative service
  • Return friendly error message
end note

@enduml

